This paper is primarily focused on generating synthetic provenance graphs and evaluating their quality, which falls under the domain of database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of graph algorithms for provenance analytics, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the testing of storage and query capabilities of provenance management systems, which is related to computer security (cs.CR). The use of a custom Domain Specific Language for expressing constraints is a topic of interest in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Neo4J, a popular graph database management system, which falls under the domain of software engineering (cs.SE).
